- Easier to refactor UI without touching update logic

### 3. Keyboard Handling → Extract Router

Create `src/meal_planner/cli/screens/fatsecret_diary_keyboard.gleam`:

```gleam
pub fn handle_key_press(model: DiaryModel, key: String) -> DiaryMsg {
  case model.view_state {
    MainView -> handle_main_view_key(key)
    SearchPopup -> handle_search_popup_key(key)
    DatePicker(_) -> handle_date_picker_key(key)
    EditAmount(_) -> handle_edit_popup_key(key)
    ConfirmDelete(_) -> handle_delete_confirm_key(key)
  }
}

// 50+ lines of specific handlers extracted
fn handle_main_view_key(key: String) -> DiaryMsg { ... }
fn handle_search_popup_key(key: String) -> DiaryMsg { ... }
```

Benefits:
- Update function drops 60 lines of key handling
- Keyboard layout documented in one place
- Easy to add/modify bindings

### 4. State Helpers → Constructor Functions

```gleam
// Reduce boilerplate in init and update
pub fn init_diary_model(config: Config) -> DiaryModel {
  DiaryModel(
    current_date: today_as_date_int(),
    entries_by_meal: [],
    nutrition_targets: None,
    daily_totals: NutritionTotals(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0),
    search_state: SearchState(False, "", [], 0, False),
    edit_state: None,
    delete_confirmation: None,
    view_state: MainView,
    loading: False,
    error: None,
    food_cache: dict.new(),
    pagination: PaginationState(0, 50),
  )
}

pub fn clear_error(model: DiaryModel) -> DiaryModel {
  DiaryModel(..model, error: None)
}

pub fn set_error(model: DiaryModel, msg: String) -> DiaryModel {
  DiaryModel(..model, error: Some(msg), loading: False)
}
```

### 5. Message Handling → Pattern Grouping

Reorganize update function:

```gleam
pub fn update(model: DiaryModel, msg: DiaryMsg) -> #(DiaryModel, List(fn() -> DiaryMsg)) {
  case msg {
    // Date navigation (6 cases)
    DateNavigatePrevious -> handle_date_navigate(model, -1)
    DateNavigateNext -> handle_date_navigate(model, 1)
    DateJumpToToday -> handle_date_jump_today(model)
    DateShowPicker -> handle_date_show_picker(model)
    DateConfirmPicker(date_str) -> handle_date_confirm_picker(model, date_str)
    DateCancelPicker -> handle_date_cancel_picker(model)

    // Entry management (12 cases)
    AddEntryStart -> handle_add_entry_start(model)
    SearchFoodStarted(q) -> handle_search_started(model, q)
    // ... etc

    // Server operations (8 cases)
    FetchEntriesForDate -> handle_fetch_entries(model)
    GotDailyEntries(r) -> handle_got_daily_entries(model, r)
    // ... etc
  }
}

// Helper functions reduce nesting
fn handle_date_navigate(model: DiaryModel, offset: Int) -> #(DiaryModel, List(...)) {
  let new_date = model.current_date + offset
  let updated_model = DiaryModel(..model, current_date: new_date)
  #(updated_model, [fetch_entries_for_date(new_date)])
}
```

### 6. Type Conversions → Explicit Functions

```gleam
// Instead of inline conversion strings
pub fn meal_type_to_display(meal: diary_types.MealType) -> String {
  case meal {
    diary_types.Breakfast -> "BREAKFAST"
    diary_types.Lunch -> "LUNCH"
    diary_types.Dinner -> "DINNER"
    diary_types.Snack -> "SNACKS"
  }
}

pub fn comparison_status_to_color(status: ComparisonStatus) -> style.Color {
  case status {
    Under -> style.Red
    Met -> style.Green
    Over -> style.Red
  }
}

pub fn comparison_status_to_symbol(status: ComparisonStatus) -> String {
  case status {
    Under -> "▼ Under"
    Met -> "✓ On Track"
    Over -> "▲ Over"
  }
}
```

### 7. Validation & Parsing → Dedicated Module

Create `src/meal_planner/cli/screens/fatsecret_diary_validation.gleam`:

```gleam
pub fn validate_servings(input: String) -> Result(Float, String) {
  input
  |> string.trim
  |> float.parse
  |> result.map_error(fn(_) { "Invalid number" })
  |> result.try(fn(n) {
    case n >. 0.0 {
      True -> Ok(n)
      False -> Error("Servings must be greater than 0")
    }
  })
}

pub fn validate_date(input: String) -> Result(Int, String) {
  case diary_types.date_to_int(input) {
    Ok(date_int) -> Ok(date_int)
    Error(_) -> Error("Invalid date format. Use YYYY-MM-DD")
  }
}
```

## Code Metrics (Before → After)

| Metric | Before | After | Reduction |
|--------|--------|-------|-----------|
| Main file lines | 800 | 350 | 56% |
| Update function | 400 | 180 | 55% |
| View function | 300 | 80 | 73% |
| Nesting depth | 5 | 2 | 60% |
| Functions (total) | 8 | 25+ | +212% |
| Module count | 1 | 4 | +300% |

## Gleam Formatting & Standards

All refactored code must:
- Pass `gleam format --check`
- Use `|>` pipeline operator consistently
- Extract >20 line functions
- Document public functions with `///` comments
- Use exhaustive pattern matching (no catch-all `_` unless necessary)
- Label all functions with >2 arguments
- Use opaque types for domain concepts

## Testing Refactoring

No test changes required:
- Behavior remains identical
- API contracts unchanged
- Same test assertions pass

